In this case, the host's MAC address is "8a:00:12:3e:d6:be." They detect and address LAN devices (LAN). The host connects to the router (default gateway) to visit the webpage using MAC addresses. The host requests the router's "135.168.1.1" MAC address using ARP (Address Resolution Protocol). The router sends an ARP reply with its MAC address, enabling the host to connect. MAC addresses identify and address LAN devices. The host uses the ARP protocol to connect to the router. 